default hard evidence that this does improve the
default situation?
defaultGerald defaultHolthamdefault: 
defaultInternationally
default,
default there is some evidence that fiscal devolution leads to
default a flattening of tax schedules 
defaultbecause tax competition is more effective at the top end. People on basic rate tax do not move because the basic rate changes. If you think about it, putting a penny on the basic rate cannot cost anybody more than £300 or £400
default a year
default, which does not pay for a removal van
default;
default so nobody is going anywhere. But if you start taxing millionaires, they can move around. 
defaultT
defaulthe presence of tax devolution means that there is some tax competition among authorities
default,
default and that does tend to flatten tax schedules. I do not know whether you would count that as 
defaulta 
defaultresponsibility
default,
default but it shows 
defaultthat 
defaultpeople are responsive to the opportunities that tax devolution affords them.
