defaultnational insurance, which is like income tax, but, in my view, for other reasons should not be decentralised; and there is income tax. As Gerry says, income tax is spread across the population
default—
defaulta lot of people pay it
default—and it is also very perceptible;
default people notice it. If you ask someone about tax 
defaultrates, most often they would begin by talking about income tax rates. So it is a good tax for devolution because it can be decentralised and it is noticeable.
